She is an angel lent to us. She must be returned in one piece.

At about 9:30 am on the 28th, a 27-year-old female nurse of the 7th Group of Guangxi anti-epidemic medical team from Hubei Province collapsed in the buffer zone after leaving the isolation ward in the Wuhan Union Hospital.

At the time of the incident, she was taking off her protective clothing; by all accounts, she had just finished her shift.

During the outbreak, the Wuhan Union Hospital assembled the nation's top level critical care experts and resources. After the cleaning staff found, a number of experts immediately on this nurse Liang surnamed rescue recovery, the whole process breathtaking.

In the Intensive Care Unit of the Wuhan Union Hospital, she described the procedure in detail -- as a first aid procedure

On the morning of the 28th, just after I finished my shift, leaving my new colleagues to be told what to do, I went to put on the equipment to see the patients in the quarantine area. As soon as I put on my hazmat suit, I heard over the Intercom: someone's in cardiac arrest in the buffer zone on the 8th floor. Call ICU.

I grabbed a screen and yelled at everyone: I'll go first!

Passing our ward, I double-checked that it was on the 8th floor and rushed to the dirt elevator to take the elevator.

As soon as I stepped out of the elevator, I was in the hallway screaming, where can I get help?

At the same time, I saw a staff member rush into the door of a ward, and I ran in after him. I saw a large crowd around a bed. Already, doctors were giving chest compressions to people lying on the bed, and there were people at the head of the bed kneading rubber balls with masks, people are still getting shots.

I said out loud, I'm from ICU! My colleague, who was doing chest compressions, immediately gave me his seat.

Hand-to-hand, I looked at the Ekg, ekg was negative, pulse was negative, blood pressure was negative, O2 sats fluctuated between 88 and 95% .

"An adrenaline shot! " I said as I pressed.

At this point, the first responders had decided to move the cardiac-arrest colleague from the multi-room to a suction-ready room, and I climbed into bed, kneeling on the colleague's side to give her chest compressions, the other rescue colleagues together pushed the bed to the emergency room.

The colleague in charge of kneading the ball with the head mask kept shouting: "oxygen saturation can not be maintained, quick oxygen, tracheal intubation immediately... " I quickly said don't panic, this lung is good, the ball can be squeezed into the air, lifting his jaw without intubation also worked, pulling his hand to the angle of his jaw as he pressed his chest and shouted, "more epi! GET THE DEFIBRILLATOR! Get the scissors and cut it all off! "

For a short time, whether it was 3 minutes or 5 minutes, I had no idea, defibrillator, laryngoscope have been sent; I stopped, see heart monitor prompt ventricular fibrillation..

"150 joules, defibrillate, now! " After a colleague defibrillated, I continued to press, let go, still v-fib, I suddenly felt cold sweat, clothes are wet, all over the weakness..

Because there were no witnesses, and I didn't know how long I'd been out, and I was so afraid my heart wouldn't beat back.

I'll call the switch! To prepare their own defibrillator, let push epinephrine and other drugs, at this time do artificial ventilation colleagues also began tracheal intubation, did not go in the first time, after the replacement of the catheter successfully; see him intubate, I asked everyone to move away, press the two electrodes firmly on the chest defibrillation position, press the button hard, and then do chest compressions again immediately... soon heard someone call: There is a heartbeat!

Let Go, a colleague has been touching the femoral artery, said there is a pulse, and then look at the heart rate on the stable at 120 beats per minute, the eighth floor of the doctor also pushed a suction machine connected.

At this point all the people involved in the rescue were out of breath, could not help but clap a few hands, I let half a bottle of Sodium bicarbonate to see a doctor acidosis, blood gas.

At this point, the colleague who intubated the patient introduced himself as director Xiao of the anesthesiology department. When I asked which hospital the anesthesiology department was, he said that it was the hospital of Concord. Think of the beginning of the time also correct the action of others, it is really awkward, good in goggles, screen, others can not see; this just notify each other unit, the delivery machine to work on the 8th floor of Beijing Xuanwu Hospital ICU Director Li! Help me keep feeling the femoral pulse to see if the compressions are effective, says Gao (as if) , director of Thoracic Surgery at the 14th floor hospital affiliated to China Medical University.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Blood gas showed a Ph of only 6.8, lactic acid is also high, blood potassium is only 2 points, pupil a little big, and then gave the patient an ultrasound, heart function is good, ordered potassium treatment. Initial estimates suggest ventricular fibrillation and sudden cardiac death due to hypokalemia.

After the situation is relatively stable, director Xiao and several other major said that I continue to preside over rescue, they first withdraw. I let people find some ice to do an ice cap, continue to supplement potassium, ask director Li to help lower the oxygen concentration of the machine, and conveniently put a deep vein catheter treatment. Half an hour later, and then see the pupil narrowed a bit, people will move a few, heart rate and blood pressure stable, and asked people to hang two bottles of albumin dehydration point.

After a call with the experts, I went back to cory and asked the ICU nurse if there was a director Xiao in the anesthesiology department. They said yes. I said we were working together to save my colleagues from cardiac arrest, i'm the one who made you do the chest compressions when you showed up, and I was the one who defibrillated the first time; another nurse said she was the one who brought the defibrillator and the intubation tube.

A Han nurse walks out of the ward of the First Affiliated Hospital of Guangdong Pharmaceutical University

SYNC: ytet-gagegao

May All the medical personnel who have been "loaned" to Hubei come back safely

Liang, a 27-year-old nurse at a hospital in Nanning, wrote a letter of invitation to join the Hubei anti-epidemic medical team at a critical time for the prevention and control of the epidemic, Guangxi daily reported, on February 21, he went to Hubei Province with the medical team to support the prevention and control of NCP, and worked in the West Hospital of Wuhan Union Medical College Hospital according to the unified arrangement of the state.

As of this push, we know through relevant channels, this young and brave colleague is still in the rescue treatment, consciousness is still not recovered.

Colleagues at the Wuhan Union Hospital said that all the people of the All China Federation and all Wuhan were concerned about her because she was an angel lent to us by the people of Guangxi! We must return it in one piece!

According to the blood gas test results of the nurse mentioned above, the Ph value of her body was only 6.8, indicating severe acidosis. We normal people are in the 7.35-7.45 range, which is a very serious number.

In addition, the normal blood potassium range of 3.5-5.5, hyperkalemia and hypokalemia may cause malignant Arrhythmia, or even sudden death. The nurse's blood potassium is only 2 points, analysis of its causes, it is likely to be poor diet, long time to wear protective clothing caused by excessive sweating, hypoxia is very severe.

All in all, high-intensity work, wearing protective clothing all day sweating, eating and urinating are not regular, may be the cause of hypokalemia.

[ Chen Jing, Ward 1, Department of Critical Care Medicine at Vulcan Mountain Hospital, and head nurse, Department of Kidney Medicine at Long March Hospital of Naval Medical University, describes the hardships of working in protective clothing. ]

Under the epidemic, from all over the country's medical personnel retrograde Wuhan, they are ordinary people, but also have the courage of perseverance and Bodhisattva angels. High-intensity work, tense mood, airtight protective clothing, irregular diet, inconvenience to defecate and urinate, as well as lack of sleep, may lead to a lack of water, electrolyte disorders, etc. , it can also lead to ventricular fibrillation and sudden death.

Here, we appeal to our colleagues not to "show off" by relying on their young bodies and strong hearts. If conditions permit, they should not drink pure water, but water containing sodium ions and potassium ions. Leaders should also guard the bottom line, ensure that front-line medical workers 4-6 hours shift system, so that they can fully rest, timely replenishment of water and nutrition, timely psychological counseling.

May All the medical staff in Hubei come back safe and sound!

Hope that all medical workers in the field can take care of themselves and enjoy the sunshine after the outbreak is over!
